Result: true  
Justification: The claim "Dr. Lubber is not meticulous" is logically entailed by the given information. The conditional "If Dr. Lubber is meticulous, then he produces accurate results and gains international recognition" is given, and it is known that Dr. Lubber produces accurate results. However, gaining international recognition requires both conducting thorough research and developing innovative methods (from "For any researcher who gains international recognition, they must conduct thorough research and develop innovative methods"). Dr. Lubber does not develop innovative methods (since if he did, he would make new discoveries, but he does not), and he does not conduct thorough research (as he does not analyze his findings, and thorough research likely involves analysis). Therefore, he does not gain international recognition, making the consequent of the meticulousness conditional false. For the conditional to hold, the antecedent must be false, so Dr. Lubber is not meticulous.